# H5 Tower Defense — Project Summary

## Concept

Single-player mobile tower defense, portrait orientation, for Meta Horizon Worlds.
The player places towers on a 9×12 grid during build phases to stop waves of enemies from crossing the path.
Core tension: strategic placement (choke points, range overlap) vs. economy management (gold per kill vs. wave escalation).

---

## Platform & Stack

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| Platform | Meta Horizon Studio (MHS) |
| Language | TypeScript ES2022 |
| Target | Mobile portrait, local single-player |
| Grid | 9 × 12 world units, centered on origin |
| Play area | Grid ~70% screen height; HUD top ~10%, Shop bottom ~20% |

---

## Architecture

### Principle
Event-driven, no direct component references. Each service owns one responsibility.
New features are new files — when possible existing files are not modified.

### Communication
All gameplay communication via `EventService.sendLocally()`.

### Pipeline Services
Three resolution pipelines — each is a reduce over registered modifier closures:

| Service | Pipeline | Current modifiers |
|---------|----------|-------------------|
| `HitService` | `IHitContext → IHitContext` | `SplashSystem` (AoE expansion) |
| `DamageService` | `IDamageContext → IDamageContext` | *(none — passthrough)* |
| `DebuffService` | `IDebuffContext → IDebuffContext` | `DebuffSystem` (slow application) |

Adding a new mechanic (chain, pierce, burn…) = one new service file + one import in `GameManager._services`.

### Tower Placement Flow
```
Drag start   → PlacementService spawns preview + RangeIndicator (same template, tinted)
Drag move    → Preview snaps to nearest cell, green (valid) / red (invalid)
Drag release → valid: GridTapped event → TowerService._tryPlace() → spawn real tower
             → invalid or out-of-bounds: preview destroyed, action cancelled
```

---

## File Structure

```
Scripts/
  Types.ts          — Enums, interfaces, pipeline contexts, all LocalEvents
  Constants.ts      — Grid dims, timing, economy values
  Assets.ts         — ALL TemplateAsset declarations (single source of truth)

  Defs/
    TowerDefs.ts    — TOWER_DEFS: ITowerDef[] (4 towers)
    EnemyDefs.ts    — ENEMY_DEFS: IEnemyDef[] (4 enemy types)
    LevelDefs.ts    — LEVEL_DEFS: ILevelDef[] (10 waves, 1 level)
    PathDefs.ts     — PATH_WAYPOINTS_LEVEL_0 (snake path top→bottom)

  Services/
    TowerCatalog    — find(id), all() from TOWER_DEFS
    EnemyCatalog    — find(id), all() from ENEMY_DEFS
    PathService     — waypoint path, cellToWorld(), isPathCell()
    TowerRegistry   — grid occupancy, registered towers
    EnemyRegistry   — live enemy positions (worldX, worldZ, pathT, hp)
    ResourceService — gold, lives, earn(), spend(), loseLife()
    TargetingService — getBestTarget(), getEnemiesInRadius()
    TowerService    — selectedId, place on GridTapped
    EnemySpawnService — tick-based wave spawn queue
    WaveService     — state machine: Build → Wave → WaveClear → loop
    PlacementService — drag-to-place input handler
    HitService      — hit target expansion pipeline
    DamageService   — damage value pipeline
    DebuffService   — debuff application pipeline
    SplashSystem    — registers AoE modifier into HitService
    DebuffSystem    — registers slow modifier into DebuffService

  Components/
    GameManager     — onUpdate tick, forces service init order
    ClientSetup     — camera (Fixed mode), FocusedInteraction enable
    TowerController — per-frame targeting + firing
    EnemyController — path follow, debuff state, die/reach-end
    ProjectileController — homing, detonate via pipelines
```

